        caption: String.raw`The recursive Kronecker encoder for $N=4$, the fast transform behind $\mathbf x=\mathbf u G_N$ with $G_N=B_N F^{\otimes n}$. Four wires carry the inputs $u_1..u_4$ left to right through $\log_2 4=2$ butterfly stages: stage 1 (teal) XORs adjacent pairs (span 1), stage 2 (orange) XORs across span 2, producing $x_1=u_1\oplus u_2\oplus u_3\oplus u_4$, $x_2=u_2\oplus u_4$, $x_3=u_3\oplus u_4$, $x_4=u_4$ — exactly the columns of $F^{\otimes 2}$. The same butterfly extends to any $N=2^n$: it has $\tfrac{N}{2}\log_2 N$ XOR gates (so encoding is $O(N\log N)$ and $G_N$ is never formed explicitly), while the full matrix $F^{\otimes n}$ carries $3^n$ ones. The decoder runs this identical graph backwards.`
